{{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Latin America. Non-Wester and Western philosophy]] |era = [[Latin American philosophy and Indigenous and popular thought. Decolonial philosophy. Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy. ]] |color = |image = |name = '''Alejandro Arturo Vallega Arredondo''' |birth_date = February 18, 1964 |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Continental philosophy]] | institutions = [[University of Oregon]] |main_interests = [[Latin American thought]], [[Philosophy of liberation]], [[Decolonial philosophies]], [[Hermeneutics]], [[Deconstruction]] |notable_ideas =Liberatory decolonial aesthetic though. | spouse = | education = | alma_mater = [[University of Vienna]] |influences = [[Enrique Dussel, Rodolfo Kusch, Martin Heidegger, Jacques Derrida.]], |influenced = |awards = Rippey Innovation Teaching Award 2018-2019 Robert F. and Evelyn Nelson Wulf Professorship in the Humanities. }}
'''Alejandro Arturo Vallega Arredondo''' (born February 18, 1964) is a Chilean-born philosopher, writer, painter and associate professor of [[philosophy]] at the [[University of Oregon]]. He is known for his expertise on Latin American and decolonial philosophy as well as [[hermeneutics]] and [[deconstruction]].<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Malpas|first1=Jeff|title=Review of Heidegger and the Issue of Space. Thinking on Exilic Grounds|journal=[[Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews]]|date=11 June 2004|url=http://ndpr.nd.edu/news/heidegger-and-the-issue-of-space-thinking-on-exilic-grounds/|issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Rivera|first1=Omar|title=Reading Alejandro Vallega Toward a Decolonial Aesthetics|journal=[[Comparative and Continental Philosophy]]|volume=9|issue=2|pages=162–173|doi=10.1080/17570638.2017.1335030|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/17570638.2017.1335030|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref> Vallega is the president of [[North American Society for Philosophical Hermeneutics]]. He has developed the aesthetic dimension of Philosophy of Liberation and decolonial thought. He is the editor of the English version of Enrique Dussel's ''Ethics of Liberation''.
==Books== *''Heidegger and the Question of Space: Thinking on Exilic Grounds'' (Penn State Press, 1999) *''Sense and Finitude: Encounters at the Limit of Language, Art, and the Political'' (SUNY press, 2009-2010) *''Latin American Philosophy from Identity to Radical Exteriority'' (Indiana University Press, 2014) *Dussel, Enrique. ''Ethics of Liberation: In the Age of Globalisation and Exclusion.'' Ed. Alejandro Vallega (Duke University Press, 2013)
