{{Infobox language |name=Berom |nativename=Birom |states=[[Nigeria]] |region=[[Plateau State]] |ethnicity=[[Berom people]] |speakers=1 million |date=2010 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Plateau languages|Plateau]] |fam4=[[Beromic languages|Beromic]] |iso3=bom |glotto=bero1242 |glottorefname=Berom }} '''Berom''' (Birom) is a [[Plateau language]] of [[Nigeria]]. The language is locally numerically important and is consistently spoken by [[Berom people|Berom]] of all ages in rural areas. However, the Berom are shifting to [[Hausa language|Hausa]] in cities.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ethnologue.com/18/language/bom/|title=Berom|work=Ethnologue|access-date=2017-07-24}}</ref>
The small Cen and Nincut dialects may be separate languages.
