'''Edward Francis Harris''' (13 May 1834&ndash;26 July 1898) was a New Zealand public servant, interpreter, landowner, genealogist. Of [[Māori people|Māori]] descent, he identified with the [[Rongowhakaata]] and [[Te Aitanga-a-Hauiti]] [[iwi]]. He was born in [[Gisborne, New Zealand|Gisborne]], [[North Island|East Coast]], [[New Zealand]] on 13 May 1834.<ref name="DNZB Harris">{{DNZB|title=Edward Francis Harris|first= R. De Z.|last= Hall|id=2h14|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>
