{{Infobox person |name = Einar Økland |image = Einar Økland @ Oslo bokfestival 2011.jpg |image_size = |alt = Portrait of Einar Økland |caption = Einar Økland in 2011 |birth_name = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age |1940|1|17|df=y}} |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |nationality = Norwegian |occupation = Poet, playwright, essayist and children's writer | spouse = | children = | parents = | relatives = |known_for = |notable_works= |awards = }}
'''Einar Økland''' (born 17 January 1940) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] poet, playwright, essayist and children's writer.
He was born in [[Sveio]], and educated psychologist.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Einar Økland |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Øystein |last=Rottem |authorlink=Øystein Rottem |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Einar_Økland/utdypning |language=Norwegian |accessdate=28 April 2015 }}</ref>
He made his literary debut in 1963, with the poetry collection ''Ein gul dag''.<ref name=samlaget-okland>{{cite web |url=http://www.samlaget.no/Forfattarar/OE/Einar-OEkland.aspx|title=Einar Økland |publisher=Samlaget |date= |language=Norwegian |accessdate=28 April 2015}}</ref> He was awarded the [[Melsom Prize]] 1991 for ''Når ikkje anna er sagt'',<ref name=samlaget-okland/> and the [[Dobloug Prize]] in 2000.<ref name=samlaget-okland/><ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Einar Økland |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor-last=Godal | editor-first=Anne Marit | editor-link=Anne Marit Godal |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Einar_Økland |language=Norwegian|accessdate=28 April 2015}}</ref>
== Awards == *[[Norwegian Critics Prize for Literature]] 1978 *[[Aschehoug Prize]] 1988 *[[Melsom Prize]] 1992 *[[Nynorsk Literature Prize]] 1993 *[[Dobloug Prize]] 2000 *[[Gyldendal Prize]] 2007 *[[Språkprisen]] 2015 *[[Brage Prize]] Honorary Award 2015
