{{Infobox language |name=Ndogo |nativename= |region=[[South Sudan]] |ethnicity=[[Ndogo people|Ndogo]] |speakers=20,000 |date=2011 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam1=[[Ubangian languages|Ubangian]] |fam2=Seri–Mba |fam3=[[Sere languages|Sere]] |fam4=Sere–Bviri |iso3=ndz |glotto=ndog1248 |glottorefname=Ndogo }}
'''Ndogo''' is a [[Ubangian language]], one of the nine major languages of [[South Sudan]], and is taught in primary school. It is used as a secondary language by the [[Gollo people|Gollo]] and some of the [[Gbaya people|Gbaya]], among others.
